default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultS
defaulttreet
defaultG
defaultames
default has recently commissio
defaultned research work related to the concept of sporting capital, which is analogous to the theory o
defaultf human capital and defined as the stock of physical, social an
defaultd psychological attributes and competencies that support and motivate an individual to participate in sport and to sustain that participation over time'. The study investigated the relationship between an 
defaultindividual’s
default sporting capital (made up of 3 domains
default - social, physical and psychological) and the likelihood of participating in sport using data from Sport England APS6 survey. 
default1.19
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe research indicated a clear relationship between sporting capital and the probability of participating in sport - so individu
defaultals with a high SC score were much likely to be participating than those with a low score. The research also highlighted structural inequalities - for example on average males had much higher scores than females as did those from higher socio- economic gro
defaultups. In particular - women scored much lower than men in the psychological domain and questions relating to body confidence. Therefore, interventions aimed at engaging females are much more likely to succeed if they include elements aimed at raising confid
defaultence, self-esteem and body image as well as tacking physical barriers.
